description:
File: rust/lichen-meshtastic/src/bridge.rs:183-209

When processing IP_TUNNEL_APP packets, the code only validates minimum header size (40 bytes) but does not validate the IPv6 version field:

```rust
PortNum::IpTunnelApp => {
    if data.payload.len() < 40 {
        return Err(BridgeError::InvalidPacket);
    }
    // Extract src/dst from IPv6 header without checking version
    let src_bytes: [u8; 16] = data.payload[8..24]...
```

The first 4 bits of byte 0 should equal 6 for IPv6. Without this check:

1. IPv4 packets (version 4) could be misinterpreted as IPv6
2. Malformed/corrupted packets proceed through the stack
3. Address extraction from wrong offsets could occur

IMPACT: Malformed packets are not rejected early, potentially causing downstream confusion or security issues.

FIX: Add version validation:
```rust
if (data.payload[0] >> 4) != 6 {
    return Err(BridgeError::InvalidPacket);
}
```
